      • findMibSymbol

        public MibValueSymbol findMibSymbol(java.lang.String oid)
        Searches the OID tree from the loaded MIB files for the best matching value. The returned OID symbol will have the longest matching OID value, but doesn't have to be an exact match. The search requires the full numeric OID value (from the root).
        Parameters:
        oid - the numeric OID string to search for
        Returns:
        the best matching OID symbol, or null if no partial match was found
        Since:
        2.10
        See Also:
        MibLoader.getOid(String)
